java terminal: -----

npm create vite@latest 
    - creates new js project with essentials

npm install
    - install everything else needed

npm install three
    - installs three.js. you must do this every time you make a new site
    
npm run dev 
    - starts local server

---------------------------

html: --------

note tag = <!--      -->

<br> = a line break 
<span> = allows you to select a specific part of text inside of an <h> tag

section.section = class shortcut

.box = div class shortcut

npx serv = starts a basic server for hthml site
css: -------------------

note tag = /* */ = shortcut = ctrl + /

gradient and fit to screen = 
    #root {
  width: 100vw;
  height: 100vh;
  background-color: #1d1d36;
  background-image: linear-gradient(0deg, #b2ffde 0%, #efefef 100%);
}

body,html {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

